This paper is about using smaller datasets to accelerate the training of machine learning models, specifically for hyperparameter search. The paper focuses on image datasets, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses neural networks and algorithmic approaches, which are common topics in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions synthetic examples and data distillation, which are techniques commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.CL and cs.NE.
